question:
District category contains Single-family Homes, Industrial District, and Shopping District.
Supermarkets category contains Stop & Shop, Morrisons, King Soopers, and Grocery Outlet.
Product category contains Cakes, Pudding, and Canned Pumpkin.
Ingredient category contains Flaxseed Oil, Cardamom, and Molasses.
The number of each Shopping District 's Grocery Outlet equals 21.
The number of each Canned Pumpkin 's Cardamom equals each Shopping District 's Morrisons.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Cakes equals each Pudding 's Flaxseed Oil.
The number of each Pudding 's Cardamom equals each Canned Pumpkin 's Molasses.
The number of each Industrial District 's King Soopers equals each Industrial District 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Cakes equals 9 times each Single-family Homes 's King Soopers.
The number of each King Soopers 's Canned Pumpkin equals 19 times each Single-family Homes 's Stop & Shop.
The number of each Cakes 's Flaxseed Oil equals 7 more than each Canned Pumpkin 's Molasses.
The number of each Industrial District 's Grocery Outlet equals 20 times each Stop & Shop 's Cakes.
The number of each Cakes 's Molasses equals 12 times each Stop & Shop 's Cakes.
The number of each Morrisons 's Pudding equals each Canned Pumpkin 's Molasses.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Stop & Shop equals 18.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's King Soopers equals 3 more than each Canned Pumpkin 's Cardamom.
The number of each Pudding 's Flaxseed Oil equals the difference of each King Soopers 's Canned Pumpkin and each Single-family Homes 's Stop & Shop.
The number of each Shopping District 's Morrisons equals 5 more than each Industrial District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Canned Pumpkin 's Molasses equals 0.
How many Cakes does Grocery Outlet have?
solution:
Define each Single-family Homes 's Stop & Shop as x; So x = 18.
Define each King Soopers 's Canned Pumpkin as I; So I = 19 * x = 19 * 18 = 20.
Define each Pudding 's Flaxseed Oil as h; So h = I - x = 20 - 18 = 2.
Define each Stop & Shop 's Cakes as C; So C = h = 2.
Define each Industrial District 's Grocery Outlet as j; So j = 20 * C = 20 * 2 = 17.
Define each Industrial District 's King Soopers as y; So y = j = 17.
Define each Industrial District 's Supermarkets as U; So U = j + y = 17 + 17 = 11.
Define each Shopping District 's Morrisons as Z; So Z = 5 + U = 5 + 11 = 16.
Define each Canned Pumpkin 's Cardamom as F; So F = Z = 16.
Define each Single-family Homes 's King Soopers as H; So H = 3 + F = 3 + 16 = 19.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Cakes as v; So v = 9 * H = 9 * 19 = 10.
